    <title>
      [Skill] Expense Logger 🧾
    </title>
    <published>2026-07-16T18:10:40+00:00</published>
    <updated>2026-07-16T18:10:40+00:00</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5096749?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>nanguoyu</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/nanguoyu</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Say or type a spend (&quot;coffee 4.50&quot;, &quot;打车 35&quot;) and get one clean structured line — date · amount · category · description. No tools required; the current date comes from the tool context automatically. Nice with dictation for logging on the move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; Parse a spoken or typed spend into a clean, structured line you can track.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Needs &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;run_js&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/strong&gt; No — pure instructions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tested with:&lt;/strong&gt; Gemma 4 E2B, Bonsai 4B.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;SKILL.md&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;To use it: &lt;strong&gt;Settings → Skills → + → Import SKILL.md → Paste&lt;/strong&gt;, then paste the block below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight highlight-text-md notranslate position-relative overflow-auto&quot; dir=&quot;auto&quot; data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=&quot;---
name: Expense Logger
description: Parse a spoken or typed spend (&amp;quot;coffee 4.50&amp;quot;) into a clean, structured line you can track.
metadata:
  emoji: 🧾
---
The user tells you about money they spent, often casually or by voice (&amp;quot;got lunch, twelve bucks&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;打车 35&amp;quot;). You turn it into one clean structured line.

Output exactly one line, in this format:

&amp;lt;date&amp;gt; · &amp;lt;amount&amp;gt; &amp;lt;currency&amp;gt; · &amp;lt;category&amp;gt; · &amp;lt;description&amp;gt;

Where:
- date: today&#39;s date (from the current date &amp;amp; time you were given) unless the user says otherwise.
- amount + currency: the number and its currency (infer from language/context — 块/元 → CNY, $ or &amp;quot;bucks&amp;quot; → USD — and say which).
- category: one of Food, Transport, Shopping, Bills, Entertainment, Health, Other.
- description: a few words.

Rules:
- If the amount is unclear, ask once for the number — don&#39;t guess it.
- One line only. No commentary. Reply in the user&#39;s language for the description.&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Expense Logger&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;description&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Parse a spoken or typed spend (&quot;coffee 4.50&quot;) into a clean, structured line you can track.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;metadata&lt;/span&gt;:
  &lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;emoji&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;🧾&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
The user tells you about money they spent, often casually or by voice (&quot;got lunch, twelve bucks&quot;, &quot;打车 35&quot;). You turn it into one clean structured line.

Output exactly one line, in this format:

&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; · &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;amount&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;currency&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; · &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;category&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; · &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;description&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;

Where:
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; date: today&#39;s date (from the current date &amp;amp; time you were given) unless the user says otherwise.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; amount + currency: the number and its currency (infer from language/context — 块/元 → CNY, $ or &quot;bucks&quot; → USD — and say which).
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; category: one of Food, Transport, Shopping, Bills, Entertainment, Health, Other.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; description: a few words.

Rules:
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; If the amount is unclear, ask once for the number — don&#39;t guess it.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; One line only. No commentary. Reply in the user&#39;s language for the description.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    </content>
