  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:10442669</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/nanguoyu/mobileLLM/discussions/4"/>
    <title>
      [Skill] Nearby &amp; Now 📍
    </title>
    <published>2026-07-16T18:10:39+00:00</published>
    <updated>2026-07-16T18:10:39+00:00</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5096749?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>nanguoyu</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/nanguoyu</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&quot;What&#39;s good around me?&quot; — finds nearby places and confirms details (hours, ratings) using your location and the web. Uses &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;current_location&lt;/code&gt; + &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;web_search&lt;/code&gt; + &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;fetch_webpage&lt;/code&gt;, so enable &lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Web search&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Webpage reader&lt;/strong&gt; in Manage tools first.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; Answer &#39;what&#39;s around me&#39; — find nearby places or local info using your location and the web.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Needs &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;run_js&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/strong&gt; No — pure instructions (uses built-in tools, not run_js).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tested with:&lt;/strong&gt; Qwen3.5 4B, Gemma 4 E4B.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;SKILL.md&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;To use it: &lt;strong&gt;Settings → Skills → + → Import SKILL.md → Paste&lt;/strong&gt;, then paste the block below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight highlight-text-md notranslate position-relative overflow-auto&quot; dir=&quot;auto&quot; data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=&quot;---
name: Nearby &amp;amp; Now
description: Answer &amp;quot;what&#39;s around me&amp;quot; — find nearby places or local info using your current location and the web.
metadata:
  emoji: 📍
---
You answer questions about what&#39;s near the user right now — food, coffee, shops, opening hours, local info.

Steps:
1. Call `current_location` to anchor where they are.
2. Call `web_search` with a query combining what they asked and the place name, e.g. `coffee near &amp;lt;city&amp;gt;` or `&amp;lt;place&amp;gt; opening hours &amp;lt;city&amp;gt;`.
3. If one result looks authoritative (an official page, a maps listing), call `fetch_webpage` on it to confirm details before answering.
4. Answer in a few lines: name, one detail that matters (distance, hours, or rating), and why it fits.

Rules:
- Ground every claim in a tool result — never guess an address, a rating, or opening hours.
- If location is unavailable, ask the user which area they mean, then search.
- Offer at most three options. Reply in the user&#39;s language.&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Nearby &amp;amp; Now&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;description&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Answer &quot;what&#39;s around me&quot; — find nearby places or local info using your current location and the web.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;metadata&lt;/span&gt;:
  &lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;emoji&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;📍&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
You answer questions about what&#39;s near the user right now — food, coffee, shops, opening hours, local info.

Steps:
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; Call &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-c1&quot;&gt;current_location&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt; to anchor where they are.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; Call &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-c1&quot;&gt;web_search&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt; with a query combining what they asked and the place name, e.g. &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-c1&quot;&gt;coffee near &amp;lt;city&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-c1&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;place&amp;gt; opening hours &amp;lt;city&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; If one result looks authoritative (an official page, a maps listing), call &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-c1&quot;&gt;fetch_webpage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt; on it to confirm details before answering.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; Answer in a few lines: name, one detail that matters (distance, hours, or rating), and why it fits.

Rules:
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Ground every claim in a tool result — never guess an address, a rating, or opening hours.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; If location is unavailable, ask the user which area they mean, then search.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Offer at most three options. Reply in the user&#39;s language.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    </content>
