    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/nanguoyu/mobileLLM/discussions/3"/>
    <title>
      [Skill] Quick Reply 💬
    </title>
    <published>2026-07-16T18:10:38+00:00</published>
    <updated>2026-07-16T18:10:38+00:00</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5096749?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>nanguoyu</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/nanguoyu</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Paste a message you received; get &lt;strong&gt;three ready-to-send replies&lt;/strong&gt; — one warm, one neutral, one brief — so you just pick and copy. No tools required. Great for triaging messages on the go.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; Draft three short replies to a message — one warm, one neutral, one brief.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Needs &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;run_js&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/strong&gt; No — pure instructions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tested with:&lt;/strong&gt; Gemma 4 E2B, Qwen3.5 4B, Hunyuan 4B.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;SKILL.md&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;To use it: &lt;strong&gt;Settings → Skills → + → Import SKILL.md → Paste&lt;/strong&gt;, then paste the block below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight highlight-text-md notranslate position-relative overflow-auto&quot; dir=&quot;auto&quot; data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=&quot;---
name: Quick Reply
description: Draft three short replies to a message — one warm, one neutral, one brief — so you can pick and send.
metadata:
  emoji: 💬
---
The user pastes a message they received. You draft three replies they could send back.

Give exactly three, labelled, each ready to copy and send as-is:

Warm: &amp;lt;friendly, a little personal&amp;gt;
Neutral: &amp;lt;polite and professional&amp;gt;
Brief: &amp;lt;one short line, gets to the point&amp;gt;

Rules:
- Match the language and register of the incoming message.
- Keep each reply to one or two sentences.
- No explanations, no &amp;quot;here are your options&amp;quot; — just the three labelled lines.
- Never invent facts the user hasn&#39;t given; if a reply needs a detail you don&#39;t have, use a neutral placeholder like [time] or [name].&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Quick Reply&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;description&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Draft three short replies to a message — one warm, one neutral, one brief — so you can pick and send.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;metadata&lt;/span&gt;:
  &lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;emoji&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;💬&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
The user pastes a message they received. You draft three replies they could send back.

Give exactly three, labelled, each ready to copy and send as-is:

Warm: &amp;lt;friendly, a little personal&amp;gt;
Neutral: &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;polite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;pl-e&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;pl-e&quot;&gt;professional&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
Brief: &amp;lt;one short line, gets to the point&amp;gt;

Rules:
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Match the language and register of the incoming message.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Keep each reply to one or two sentences.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; No explanations, no &quot;here are your options&quot; — just the three labelled lines.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Never invent facts the user hasn&#39;t given; if a reply needs a detail you don&#39;t have, use a neutral placeholder like &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;time&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;name&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    </content>
