    <title>
      [Skill] Meeting Notes 📝
    </title>
    <published>2026-07-16T18:10:37+00:00</published>
    <updated>2026-07-16T18:10:37+00:00</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5096749?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>nanguoyu</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/nanguoyu</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Turn messy notes or a dictated recap into clean &lt;strong&gt;minutes&lt;/strong&gt; — Summary, Decisions, Action items, Open questions. No tools required; pairs beautifully with the mic 🎤 in the composer (dictate the recap, then run the skill).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; Turn messy meeting notes or a dictated recap into clean minutes with decisions and action items.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Needs &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;run_js&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/strong&gt; No — pure instructions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tested with:&lt;/strong&gt; Bonsai 8B, Qwen3.5 4B, Gemma 4 E2B.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;SKILL.md&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;To use it: &lt;strong&gt;Settings → Skills → + → Import SKILL.md → Paste&lt;/strong&gt;, then paste the block below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlight highlight-text-md notranslate position-relative overflow-auto&quot; dir=&quot;auto&quot; data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=&quot;---
name: Meeting Notes
description: Turn messy meeting notes or a dictated recap into clean minutes with decisions and action items.
metadata:
  emoji: 📝
---
You turn raw meeting notes — typed or dictated, often messy — into clean minutes.

Output exactly these sections, in this order, and omit any that would be empty:

## Summary
Two or three sentences: what the meeting was about and what was decided.

## Decisions
- One bullet per decision made.

## Action items
- [ ] &amp;lt;task&amp;gt; — &amp;lt;owner, if named&amp;gt; (&amp;lt;due date, if mentioned&amp;gt;)

## Open questions
- Anything left unresolved.

Rules:
- Only use what&#39;s in the notes. Do not invent owners, dates, or decisions.
- If an owner or date isn&#39;t stated, leave it out — don&#39;t guess.
- Reply in the language of the notes.&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Meeting Notes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;description&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;Turn messy meeting notes or a dictated recap into clean minutes with decisions and action items.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;metadata&lt;/span&gt;:
  &lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;emoji&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;📝&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-s&quot;&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;
You turn raw meeting notes — typed or dictated, often messy — into clean minutes.

Output exactly these sections, in this order, and omit any that would be empty:

&lt;span class=&quot;pl-mh&quot;&gt;## &lt;span class=&quot;pl-en&quot;&gt;Summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
Two or three sentences: what the meeting was about and what was decided.

&lt;span class=&quot;pl-mh&quot;&gt;## &lt;span class=&quot;pl-en&quot;&gt;Decisions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; One bullet per decision made.

&lt;span class=&quot;pl-mh&quot;&gt;## &lt;span class=&quot;pl-en&quot;&gt;Action items&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;pl-k&quot;&gt;[ ]&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;pl-ent&quot;&gt;task&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; — &amp;lt;owner, if named&amp;gt; (&amp;lt;due date, if mentioned&amp;gt;)

&lt;span class=&quot;pl-mh&quot;&gt;## &lt;span class=&quot;pl-en&quot;&gt;Open questions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Anything left unresolved.

Rules:
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Only use what&#39;s in the notes. Do not invent owners, dates, or decisions.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; If an owner or date isn&#39;t stated, leave it out — don&#39;t guess.
&lt;span class=&quot;pl-v&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; Reply in the language of the notes.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:10442663</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/nanguoyu/mobileLLM/discussions/1"/>
    <title>
      [Skill] Daily Briefing ☀️
    </title>
    <published>2026-07-16T18:10:17+00:00</published>
    <updated>2026-07-16T18:10:17+00:00</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5096749?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>nanguoyu</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/nanguoyu</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;A short morning briefing for your phone: &lt;strong&gt;your location → weather → one headline&lt;/strong&gt;, in three lines. Uses &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;current_location&lt;/code&gt; + &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;web_search&lt;/code&gt;, so turn on the &lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Web search&lt;/strong&gt; tools (Settings → Manage tools) before using it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt; A short morning briefing — weather where you are, plus one notable news headline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Needs &lt;code class=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;run_js&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/strong&gt; No — pure instructions, works on iPhone as-is.&lt;/p&gt;
